## 2. SonarCloud: "Organization key 'Matr33shka' does not exist"

Used the org **display name** instead of the org **key**. The key is the lowercase
slug in the SonarCloud URL: `https://sonarcloud.io/organizations/<KEY>/`.

Fix in the Jenkinsfile mvn command:

```
-Dsonar.organization=<correct-lowercase-org-key>
```

---

## 3. Sonar analysis OOM — "Java heap space"

Build compiled, packaged, and ran full Java analysis, then died when Sonar spawned
the Node runtime for JS/TS/CSS analysis. The ~1 GB box ran out of heap.

### Fix A — skip the JS analyzer (this is a Java/JSP app) and cap scanner heap

Add to the mvn command:

```
-Dsonar.exclusions=**/*.js,**/*.ts,**/*.css,**/*.html -Dsonar.scanner.javaOpts=-Xmx256m
```

### Fix B — cap Maven's own heap (pipeline environment block)

```groovy
environment {
    MAVEN_OPTS = "-Xmx512m"
}
```

### Fix C — real fix: more RAM

Resize the instance to `t3.small` (2 GB) or `t3.medium` (4 GB). SonarCloud's
multi-language analyzers want >= 2 GB. EC2 console -> stop instance -> change
instance type -> start (same disk, same setup).

---

## Recommended final mvn command

```groovy
sh "mvn clean verify sonar:sonar \
  -Dsonar.projectKey=freyapvasbuggywebapp \
  -Dsonar.organization=<correct-org-key> \
  -Dsonar.host.url=https://sonarcloud.io \
  -Dsonar.token=$SONAR_TOKEN \
  -Dsonar.exclusions=**/*.js,**/*.ts,**/*.css,**/*.html \
  -Dsonar.scanner.javaOpts=-Xmx256m"
```

